1) copy frame press to WP plugin folder

2) change ./core permmissions to 777 (read and write for all)

3) Modify prefix value on config/config.php (this value must be a unique one word, the plugin's name)

4) modify main.php:

	a) give a unique name for framepress core instance:
		example:
			//init framework
			require_once('.core/w2pf_init.php');
			global $FramePress;
			global $supername;   //<< UNIQUE NAME
			$supername = new $FramePress(__FILE__);

	b) add admin pages, posibilities are:

		//Custom Box
		'menu' => array(
			array(
				'page_title' => 'Page Title',
				'menu_title' => 'Box Title',
				'capability' => 'administrator',
				'menu_slug' => 'main', //<< Controller name
			),
		),

		//Custom submenu under Custom menu
		'submenu' =>array(
			array(
				'page_title' => 'Page Title',
				'menu_title' => 'Link Title',
				'capability' => 'administrator',
				'menu_slug' => 'first', //<< Controller name
				'parent_slug' => 'main' //<< Parent
			),
		);

		//For other submenus on known admin menus
		//posibilities are: dashboard, posts, media, links, pages, comments, appearance, plugins, users, tools, settings

		'dashboard' =>array( 
			array( 
				'page_title' => 'Page Title',
				'menu_title' => 'Link Title',
				'capability' => 'administrator',
				'menú_slug' => 'first', //<< Controller name
			),
		),

		For each type it posible to declare more than one
		example:

			'tools' =>array( //MENU TYPE
				array( 
					'page_title' => 'Page Title 1',
					'menu_title' => 'Tools link Title 1',
					'capability' => 'administrator', 
					'menú_slug' => 'first',
				),
				array( 
					'page_title' => 'Page Title 2',
					'menu_title' => 'Tools link Title 2',
					'capability' => 'administrator', 
					'menú_slug' => 'first', 
				),
				array( 
					'page_title' => 'Page Title 3',
					'menu_title' => 'Tools link Title 3',
					'capability' => 'administrator', 
					'menú_slug' => 'second', 
				),
			);

	c) Add actions

		array(
			'tag' => 'do_some_action', 
			'handler' => 'first',			//<< Controller name
			'function' => 'do_action_a',	//<< function to manage the action
			'is_ajax' => true,			//<< Is an action to call with ajax?
		),

		example:
		$wp_actions = array (
			array(
				'tag' => 'save_post',				//<< well known WP tag
				'handler' => 'events',
				'function' => 'action_post_page_status',
				'is_ajax' => false,
			),
			array(
				'tag' => 'wp_head',				//<< well known WP tag
				'handler' => 'meta',
				'function' => 'insert_meta',
				'is_ajax' => false,
			),
			array(
				'tag' => 'check_status',				//<< custom tag
				'handler' => 'events',
				'function' => 'check_status',
				'is_ajax' => true,
			)
		);

	d) add action and menus to framework

		$supername->Page->add($wp_pages);
		$supername->Action->add($wp_actions);

	SEE main.php TO GET A BETTER LOOK OF ALL THIS STEPS


5) Create Your controlles for the menus and actions declared

	a) class names are: prefix_value . declared name

		example:
			Class SupernameFirst { [code] }
	
	SEE controllers/first.php TO GET A BETTER LOOK OF CONTROLLERS, AND SEE WHAT CLASESS AND METHODS ARE AVAILABLES ON THEM


6) create a layout. SEE views/layouts/alayput.php


7) create a View for you functions controllers. SEE views/first/page2.php